'Eager beaver' is an English-language idiom and may refer to:

;Organizations *Eager Beaver, an achievement level in Beavers (Scouting) *Eager
Beaver Baseball Association, a baseball league for youths in London, Ontario,
Canada *Eager Beavers RFC, Canadian rugby union Touring Side which was formed in
late 2000 *Eager Beavers, nickname for the 72d Helicopter Squadron; see List of
United States Air Force helicopter squadrons
* Eager Beaver is a cover band based out of North Florida; see
  http://www.eagerbeaverband.com
* Eager Beaver is a fork lift truck used by the British military during the
  80's. Two were known too have been used in the Falkland Islands during the
  Falklands war. ;Film and literature *The Eager Beaver (1946 film), a 1946
  Warner Bros. cartoon; see Looney Tunes and Merrie Melodies filmography
  (1940â€“1949) *Eager Beaver (1977 film), a 1977 film featuring Christine De
  Shaffer *Eager Beavers (2009 TV movie), a 2009 film featuring Bridgetta
  Tomarchio *Eager Beavers (adult film series), a series of seven pornographic
  films released between 1998 and 2004 *The Eager Beaver, a lounge featured in
  Strip Tease (novel) and the adaptation Striptease (film)
